# Database Rules

## Databases in this system
| Database | Purpose | Access pattern |
|---|---|---|
| ClickHouse | Ad spend, orders, sessions, GMV — the analytics warehouse | Read-only from agents, append-only from ingestion |
| Postgres | Approval queue, outcome store, audit log, vector embeddings | Read/write from orchestrator + frontend |
| Redis | Session memory, metric cache, BullMQ job queue | Read/write from orchestrator + worker |

## Prisma schema conventions (Postgres)

### Model naming
- Models: `PascalCase` singular (`PendingAction`, not `pending_actions`)
- Fields: `camelCase`
- Enums: `PascalCase` for type, `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` for values

### Required models
```prisma
// packages/db/prisma/schema.prisma

model Signal {
  id            String   @id @default(uuid())
  entityType    String
  entityId      String
  signalType    String
  contextSnapshot Json
  firedAt       DateTime @default(now())
  insights      Insight[]
  pendingActions PendingAction[]
}

model Insight {
  id          String   @id @default(uuid())
  signalId    String
  signal      Signal   @relation(fields: [signalId], references: [id])
  severity    InsightSeverity
  title       String
  what        String
  why         String
  evidence    Json     // string[]
  confidence  Float
  agent       String
  embedding   Unsupported("vector(1536)")?  // pgvector
  createdAt   DateTime @default(now())
  outcomes    InsightOutcome[]
}

model PendingAction {
  id              String       @id @default(uuid())
  signalId        String
  signal          Signal       @relation(fields: [signalId], references: [id])
  agent           String
  actionType      String
  actionPayload   Json
  rationale       String
  expectedOutcome String
  confidence      Float
  riskLevel       RiskLevel
  classification  ActionClass
  status          ActionStatus @default(PENDING)
  approvedBy      String?
  approvedAt      DateTime?
  rejectedReason  String?
  executedAt      DateTime?
  executionResult Json?
  expiresAt       DateTime
  createdAt       DateTime     @default(now())
}

model InsightOutcome {
  id          String   @id @default(uuid())
  insightId   String
  insight     Insight  @relation(fields: [insightId], references: [id])
  measuredAt  DateTime
  metricDeltas Json    // { roas_delta: 0.15, spend_delta: -50, ... }
  outcomeScore Float   // -1.0 to 1.0: did the insight lead to a good outcome?
}

enum InsightSeverity { CRITICAL WARNING INFO }
enum RiskLevel { LOW MEDIUM HIGH }
enum ActionClass { AUTO QUEUE BLOCK }
enum ActionStatus { PENDING APPROVED REJECTED EXECUTED EXPIRED }
```

